

Laravel Blog #1

Description:

A blog is an informational site consisting of posts typically displayed in reverse 

chronological order (the most recent post appears first). Posts written under different 

categories. There are 2 different sections, User interface, where public users read the blog 

posts & add their comments for that post. Second is the admin interface, where bloggers 

will add/edit their posts. As well as, moderate the blog comments.

There should be two types of user.

1. Public user - who can see all posts ( logging in required to post the comments )

2. Admin user - who can update/manage the contents of any post after logging in.

